sublevels.theory:
Control flow lets you alter the execution path of your program. The `if-else` statement runs different code based on a condition.

```cpp
int score = 85;
if (score >= 90) {
    std::cout << "Grade A";
} else if (score >= 80) {
    std::cout << "Grade B";
} else {
    std::cout << "Grade C";
}
```

- The `if` block runs when its condition is `true`
- The `else if` block is tested when previous conditions are `false`
- The `else` block runs when all previous conditions are `false`
- Curly braces `{}` group multiple statements (always recommended)
- A non-zero integer evaluates to `true`; zero evaluates to `false`
